data scientists at quora perform research and analysis that allows the company to make optimal product decision
because quora is such a data-driven company our data scientist play a central role in the product development process by uncovering key insight from our data as a data scientist you will work closely with product manager product designer and engineer to devise appropriate measurement and metric design randomized controlled experiment build visualization and tackle hard open-ended problem that uncover usage pattern and opportunity for the company you may also develop tool and infrastructure to scale and automate the analysis that enable rapid product iteration quora ha a wide range of rich data giving you ample room for exploration and creativity examples of some project our data scientist have worked on include modeling our long-term growth improving the relevance and personalization of the homepage feed and exploratory factor analysis of user behavior we use a variety of tool -- primarily python and sql -- to analyze data and communicate result with the rest of the company for example of data science work see quora's data blog http dataquoracom
things we look for include
bs ms phd in a scientific or quantitative field
2+ year work experience
excellent statistical intuition and knowledge of various analytical approach
curiosity and passion for quora
superb communication skill and ability to explain your analysis clearly
proficiency in sql
familiarity with python or similar scripting language
passion for learning and always improving yourself and the team around you
experience in working with large data set and distributed computing tool hive redshift is a plus